Put into a sauce pan: 
1 cup brown sugar
1 cup coffee (black.)
2 cups raisins 1 cup nutmeats.
1/3 cup shortening
nutmeg, cinnamon and salt. 
Boil all together for 3 minutes and let stand till cold. Then desolve 1 tea-spoon of soda in hot water and add to cold mixture. Then add 2 cups of flour in which 1 teaspoonful of baking powder has been sifted. 
Bake in slow oven 1 hour. 
